<item>
            <title>[OPENJPA-1567] Can we relax strict group like behavior on persistence context?</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/OPENJPA-1567</link>
                <project id="12310351" key="OPENJPA">OpenJPA</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;JPA imposes a strict group-like behavior on a persistence context. If x is managed by a persistence context C then, any instance y reachable from x has to be managed by C as well. Even if y is being accessed only by reference in context C. &lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;JPA Specification version 2.0 Section 3.2.8&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&quot;It is the responsibility of the application to insure that an instance is managed in only a single persistence context. The behavior is undefined if the same Java instance is made managed in more than one persistence context.&quot;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The actual wordings of &quot;undefined&quot;, however, leave some possibility of y being managed by context C1 while being referred by another x managed in context C2. &lt;br/&gt;
The primary motivation to allow traversal (only by reference) from x to an instance y managed by another context are&lt;br/&gt;
  a) to support a more natural use case for merge() where y may not be managed by C bout nor is y modified by the merge operation&lt;br/&gt;
  b) reduce detach cost (which remains the only current way to support use case (a))&lt;/p&gt;


&lt;p&gt;Opening up this issue for a discussion....&lt;/p&gt;


